<p><strong>Discover Starfish Sandbar by floating cottage.</strong> Journey to <strong>Little Boracay</strong> for snorkeling, dining, and relaxing on a floating cottage — followed by exploring the enchanting <strong>Starfish Sandbar</strong>.</p>

<p>This is one of the most complete coastal day experiences available in Calatagan, Batangas. Two iconic natural destinations, one unforgettable day on the water.</p>

<h2>What is the Starfish Sandbar + Little Boracay Combo Tour?</h2>
<p>The combo tour pairs two of Calatagan's most remarkable natural destinations into a single full-day experience:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Little Boracay Sandbar</strong> — the famous floating cottage experience on turquoise-clear shallow water</li>
  <li><strong>Starfish Sandbar</strong> — a magical natural shallow area where live starfish can be seen in the crystal-clear water</li>
</ul>
<p>By boat, you travel between both locations with a local guide — making this the most comprehensive way to explore what Calatagan's coastline has to offer in a single day trip from Manila.</p>

<h2>Little Boracay — The First Stop</h2>
<p>Your day begins at <strong>Little Boracay sandbar</strong>. After the short boat transfer from Calatagan's coast, you arrive at the white sand sandbar and board your <strong>floating bamboo cottage</strong> — anchored directly above the shallow, turquoise-clear water.</p>
<p>The floating cottage is your base for the morning and early afternoon. From here, you can:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Snorkel</strong> in the clear coastal waters around the sandbar</li>
  <li><strong>Swim and wade</strong> in the calm, shallow water</li>
  <li><strong>Enjoy a meal</strong> on the cottage — bring packed food and drinks for the full experience</li>
  <li><strong>Relax and take in the view</strong> — open sea on all sides, white sand underfoot, blue sky above</li>
  <li><strong>Photograph and drone</strong> — the aerial views of Little Boracay are spectacular</li>
</ul>

<div class="callout">
  <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Arrive at Little Boracay early — ideally by 9 AM. The sandbar is widest and water is calmest during morning low tide.</p>
</div>

<h2>Starfish Sandbar — The Second Stop</h2>
<p>After your floating cottage session at Little Boracay, your guide takes you by boat to the <strong>Starfish Sandbar</strong> — one of Calatagan's most enchanting natural features.</p>
<p>The Starfish Sandbar is a shallow coastal area where the seafloor is home to a remarkable number of <strong>live starfish</strong> visible in the crystal-clear water. Wading through the shallow, warm water and observing the starfish up close is a genuinely magical experience — particularly for families with children.</p>

<h3>What to Expect at Starfish Sandbar</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Shallow, warm, clear water — safe for all ages</li>
  <li>Live starfish visible from the surface — no diving needed</li>
  <li>Wide open sandbar area for swimming and wading</li>
  <li>Stunning photography opportunities — especially underwater</li>
  <li>Quieter and less crowded than some other Batangas destinations</li>
</ul>

<div class="callout">
  <p><strong>Important:</strong> Please <strong>do not remove starfish</strong> from the water. They are living marine animals. Observe, photograph, and enjoy them in their natural environment. Always return them immediately if briefly lifted for a photo.</p>
</div>

